T*
(SCHOLARGRID TECHNICAL REPORT) Tj
T*
(Chapters 3 to 7 + Tech Stack + Supabase Setup SQL) Tj
T*
(Generated on 14 April 2026) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(TECH STACK) Tj
T*
(- Frontend: React 19.2.4) Tj
T*
(- Build Tool: Vite 8.0.1) Tj
T*
(- Router: react-router-dom 7.13.1) Tj
T*
(- Styling: Tailwind CSS 3.4.19 + PostCSS + Autoprefixer) Tj
T*
(- Backend Platform: Supabase \(@supabase/supabase-js 2.103.0\)) Tj
T*
(- Animation: Framer Motion 12.38.0) Tj
T*
(- Icons: lucide-react 0.577.0) Tj
T*
(- Linting: ESLint 9.39.4) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Chapter 3 - System Requirements) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3.1 Stakeholder Analysis) Tj
T*
(- Students: Need quick note discovery, upload, group chat, leaderboard, and issue reporting.) Tj
T*
(- Administrators: Need user governance, note moderation, complaint resolution, and analytics.) Tj
T*
(- Institution/Department: Needs secure, maintainable, scalable academic collaboration platform.) Tj
T*
(- Developers/Maintainers: Need modular architecture and clear service boundaries.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3.2 Functional Requirements) Tj
T*
(- FR-01: Signup and login with Supabase Auth.) Tj
T*
(- FR-02: Role-based route protection for student and admin paths.) Tj
T*
(- FR-03: Profile view/edit with avatar support.) Tj
T*
(- FR-04: Notes upload with metadata and file storage.) Tj
T*
(- FR-05: Notes search, subject filtering, and sorting.) Tj
T*
(- FR-06: Admin note moderation \(flag/unflag/delete\).) Tj
T*
(- FR-07: Group creation and join by join code.) Tj
T*
(- FR-08: Realtime group chat messaging.) Tj
T*
(- FR-09: Complaint submission and admin status/reply updates.) Tj
T*
(- FR-10: Leaderboard based on points.) Tj
T*
(- FR-11: Admin analytics dashboard.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3.3 Non-Functional Requirements) Tj
T*
(- Security: RLS policies, role checks, bucket access control, authenticated sessions.) Tj
T*
(- Performance: Indexed columns \(role, subject, flagged, points, timestamps\).) Tj
T*
(- Reliability: Managed Supabase services for auth/database/storage/realtime.) Tj
T*
(- Usability: Responsive UI and clear navigation for both roles.) Tj
T*
(- Maintainability: Service-oriented frontend modules in src/services.) Tj
T*
(- Scalability: Managed backend can scale without custom server management.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3.4 Hardware Requirements) Tj
T*
(- Client minimum: Dual-core CPU, 4 GB RAM, 1366x768 display.) Tj
T*
(- Client recommended: Quad-core CPU, 8 GB RAM, 1920x1080 display.) Tj
T*
(- Network minimum: 5 Mbps stable internet.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3.5 Software Requirements) Tj
T*
(- Node.js and npm \(LTS recommended\).) Tj
T*
(- Browser: Current Chrome/Edge/Firefox.) Tj
T*
(- Supabase project with URL and anon key in .env.) Tj
T*
(- OS: Windows, Linux, or macOS for development.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Chapter 4 - System Design) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
